<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="188" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,671,1985]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,316,706,730]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[482,547,706,729]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1878,1902]" captionTargetBox="[226,1334,194,1804]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1334,194,1824]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Alapona modesta sp. nov., male holotype. 1, anterior portion of body, dorsal view. 2, head, frontal view. 3, anterior portion of body, lateral view. 4, forewing. 5, sternite VIII, ventral view. 6, pygofer, lateral view. 7, subgenital plate, ventral view. 8, connective and styles, dorsal view. 9, style, lateral view. 10 – 12, aedeagus in lateral, dorsal, and caudal views, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217748/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">
Fig. 
<number box="[533,547,706,729]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
) without ventral spinelike process; style (
<figureCitation box="[995,1091,706,729]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1878,1902]" captionTargetBox="[226,1334,194,1804]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1334,194,1824]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Alapona modesta sp. nov., male holotype. 1, anterior portion of body, dorsal view. 2, head, frontal view. 3, anterior portion of body, lateral view. 4, forewing. 5, sternite VIII, ventral view. 6, pygofer, lateral view. 7, subgenital plate, ventral view. 8, connective and styles, dorsal view. 9, style, lateral view. 10 – 12, aedeagus in lateral, dorsal, and caudal views, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217748/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">Figs 8, 9</figureCitation>
) without preapical dorsal spine, apical sixth strongly narrowed; aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[625,752,741,764]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1878,1902]" captionTargetBox="[226,1334,194,1804]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1334,194,1824]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Alapona modesta sp. nov., male holotype. 1, anterior portion of body, dorsal view. 2, head, frontal view. 3, anterior portion of body, lateral view. 4, forewing. 5, sternite VIII, ventral view. 6, pygofer, lateral view. 7, subgenital plate, ventral view. 8, connective and styles, dorsal view. 9, style, lateral view. 10 – 12, aedeagus in lateral, dorsal, and caudal views, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217748/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">
Figs 
<number box="[684,752,741,764]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" value="11.0" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="10.0">10–12</number>
</figureCitation>
) simple, without basiventral spinelike processes, apical third directed dorsally, forming right angle with remainder of shaft, apical half with lateral ventrally-directed flanges.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="188" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,671,1985]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,441,810,834]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">Measurements (mm).</emphasis>
Male 
<typeStatus box="[508,606,810,833]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">holotype</typeStatus>
: total length 
<number box="[742,792,810,833]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" value="10.5">10.5</number>
; crown median length 
<number box="[1034,1071,810,833]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" value="0.5">0.5</number>
; transocular width 
<number box="[1273,1309,810,833]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" value="2.3">2.3</number>
; interocular width 
<number box="[225,261,845,868]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" value="1.4">1.4</number>
; pronotum median length 
<number box="[570,606,845,868]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" value="1.4">1.4</number>
; width between humeri 
<number box="[891,928,845,868]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" value="3.2">3.2</number>
; mesonotum median length 
<number box="[1257,1293,845,868]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" value="1.6">1.6</number>
; mesonotum maximum width 
<number box="[333,370,880,903]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" value="2.4">2.4</number>
; forewing length 
<number box="[557,593,880,903]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" value="8.5">8.5</number>
; forewing maximum width 
<number box="[890,926,880,903]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" value="2.6">2.6</number>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,671,1985]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,361,914,938]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">General color.</emphasis>
Body (
<figureCitation box="[442,521,914,937]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="3.[151,255,972,996]" captionTargetBox="[210,1358,256,857]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,247,948]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 13. Alapona modesta sp. nov., male holotype, body in dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217749/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">
Fig. 
<number box="[494,521,914,937]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
) with ground color light brown. Crown (
<figureCitation box="[967,1064,914,937]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1878,1902]" captionTargetBox="[226,1334,194,1804]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1334,194,1824]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Alapona modesta sp. nov., male holotype. 1, anterior portion of body, dorsal view. 2, head, frontal view. 3, anterior portion of body, lateral view. 4, forewing. 5, sternite VIII, ventral view. 6, pygofer, lateral view. 7, subgenital plate, ventral view. 8, connective and styles, dorsal view. 9, style, lateral view. 10 – 12, aedeagus in lateral, dorsal, and caudal views, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217748/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">Figs 1, 3</figureCitation>
) with pair of small rounded black spots behind each ocellus on posterior margin. Ocelli (
<figureCitation box="[738,833,949,972]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1878,1902]" captionTargetBox="[226,1334,194,1804]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1334,194,1824]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Alapona modesta sp. nov., male holotype. 1, anterior portion of body, dorsal view. 2, head, frontal view. 3, anterior portion of body, lateral view. 4, forewing. 5, sternite VIII, ventral view. 6, pygofer, lateral view. 7, subgenital plate, ventral view. 8, connective and styles, dorsal view. 9, style, lateral view. 10 – 12, aedeagus in lateral, dorsal, and caudal views, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217748/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">Figs 1, 3</figureCitation>
) reddish-brown. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[1139,1235,949,972]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1878,1902]" captionTargetBox="[226,1334,194,1804]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1334,194,1824]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Alapona modesta sp. nov., male holotype. 1, anterior portion of body, dorsal view. 2, head, frontal view. 3, anterior portion of body, lateral view. 4, forewing. 5, sternite VIII, ventral view. 6, pygofer, lateral view. 7, subgenital plate, ventral view. 8, connective and styles, dorsal view. 9, style, lateral view. 10 – 12, aedeagus in lateral, dorsal, and caudal views, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217748/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">Figs 1, 3</figureCitation>
) with two pairs of black maculae on anterior half behind each eye, inner pair elongated and outer pair rounded; black maculae under dorsopleural carinae; posterior margin black. Mesonotum (
<figureCitation box="[776,869,1018,1041]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1878,1902]" captionTargetBox="[226,1334,194,1804]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1334,194,1824]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Alapona modesta sp. nov., male holotype. 1, anterior portion of body, dorsal view. 2, head, frontal view. 3, anterior portion of body, lateral view. 4, forewing. 5, sternite VIII, ventral view. 6, pygofer, lateral view. 7, subgenital plate, ventral view. 8, connective and styles, dorsal view. 9, style, lateral view. 10 – 12, aedeagus in lateral, dorsal, and caudal views, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217748/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">Figs 1, 3</figureCitation>
) with large yellow spot on scutellum. Forewing (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1878,1902]" captionTargetBox="[226,1334,194,1804]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1334,194,1824]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Alapona modesta sp. nov., male holotype. 1, anterior portion of body, dorsal view. 2, head, frontal view. 3, anterior portion of body, lateral view. 4, forewing. 5, sternite VIII, ventral view. 6, pygofer, lateral view. 7, subgenital plate, ventral view. 8, connective and styles, dorsal view. 9, style, lateral view. 10 – 12, aedeagus in lateral, dorsal, and caudal views, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217748/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,165,1053,1076]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
) subhyaline; with numerous scattered dark brown or black maculae; venation brown. 
<collectingCountry box="[1087,1140,1053,1076]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">Hind</collectingCountry>
wing fuscous. Legs brown, except dark brown areas on apex of foretibiae, basal portion of metatibiae, and apical tarsomeres of fore and hind legs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,671,1985]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,458,1122,1146]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">External morphology.</emphasis>
Genae (
<figureCitation box="[566,640,1122,1145]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1878,1902]" captionTargetBox="[226,1334,194,1804]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1334,194,1824]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Alapona modesta sp. nov., male holotype. 1, anterior portion of body, dorsal view. 2, head, frontal view. 3, anterior portion of body, lateral view. 4, forewing. 5, sternite VIII, ventral view. 6, pygofer, lateral view. 7, subgenital plate, ventral view. 8, connective and styles, dorsal view. 9, style, lateral view. 10 – 12, aedeagus in lateral, dorsal, and caudal views, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217748/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">
Fig. 
<number box="[626,640,1122,1145]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
) broad, with group of short setae behind eyes. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[1354,1428,1122,1145]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1878,1902]" captionTargetBox="[226,1334,194,1804]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1334,194,1824]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Alapona modesta sp. nov., male holotype. 1, anterior portion of body, dorsal view. 2, head, frontal view. 3, anterior portion of body, lateral view. 4, forewing. 5, sternite VIII, ventral view. 6, pygofer, lateral view. 7, subgenital plate, ventral view. 8, connective and styles, dorsal view. 9, style, lateral view. 10 – 12, aedeagus in lateral, dorsal, and caudal views, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217748/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">
Fig. 
<number box="[1414,1428,1122,1145]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
) approximately three times longer than wide; venation distinct and simple; three closed anteapical cells, base of inner more basal than base of median cell; five apical cells (R 
<number box="[758,768,1192,1215]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" value="1.0">1</number>
present), base of third more apical than others; apex rounded; appendix present, large, and extending from claval apex to second apical cell. 
<collectingCountry box="[1026,1079,1226,1249]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">Hind</collectingCountry>
leg with plantar surface of first tarsomere with two parallel rows of setae, setae on anterior row very small.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,671,1985]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,389,1298,1322]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">Male terminalia.</emphasis>
Sternite VIII (
<figureCitation box="[544,608,1298,1321]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1878,1902]" captionTargetBox="[226,1334,194,1804]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1334,194,1824]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Alapona modesta sp. nov., male holotype. 1, anterior portion of body, dorsal view. 2, head, frontal view. 3, anterior portion of body, lateral view. 4, forewing. 5, sternite VIII, ventral view. 6, pygofer, lateral view. 7, subgenital plate, ventral view. 8, connective and styles, dorsal view. 9, style, lateral view. 10 – 12, aedeagus in lateral, dorsal, and caudal views, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217748/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">
Fig. 
<number box="[594,608,1298,1321]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
) rectangular, length about 
<number box="[894,901,1296,1309]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" value="3.0">3</number>
/ 
<number box="[909,916,1313,1326]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" value="4.0">4</number>
width; posterior margin almost straight. Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[159,224,1336,1359]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1878,1902]" captionTargetBox="[226,1334,194,1804]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1334,194,1824]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Alapona modesta sp. nov., male holotype. 1, anterior portion of body, dorsal view. 2, head, frontal view. 3, anterior portion of body, lateral view. 4, forewing. 5, sternite VIII, ventral view. 6, pygofer, lateral view. 7, subgenital plate, ventral view. 8, connective and styles, dorsal view. 9, style, lateral view. 10 – 12, aedeagus in lateral, dorsal, and caudal views, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217748/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">
Fig. 
<number box="[210,224,1336,1359]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
) moderately produced; in lateral view, trapezoidal; dorsal margin with preapical emargination; posterior margin narrowly rounded; ventral margin without process; with long robust setae on dorsomedian area; most of surface covered with minute denticuli. Valve (
<figureCitation box="[484,552,1405,1428]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1878,1902]" captionTargetBox="[226,1334,194,1804]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1334,194,1824]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Alapona modesta sp. nov., male holotype. 1, anterior portion of body, dorsal view. 2, head, frontal view. 3, anterior portion of body, lateral view. 4, forewing. 5, sternite VIII, ventral view. 6, pygofer, lateral view. 7, subgenital plate, ventral view. 8, connective and styles, dorsal view. 9, style, lateral view. 10 – 12, aedeagus in lateral, dorsal, and caudal views, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217748/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">
Fig. 
<number box="[538,552,1405,1428]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
) laterally fused to pygofer; articulated posteriorly to subgenital plates; anterior margin slightly convex; posterior margin with narrow median emargination. Subgenital plates (
<figureCitation box="[1198,1265,1440,1463]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1878,1902]" captionTargetBox="[226,1334,194,1804]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1334,194,1824]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Alapona modesta sp. nov., male holotype. 1, anterior portion of body, dorsal view. 2, head, frontal view. 3, anterior portion of body, lateral view. 4, forewing. 5, sternite VIII, ventral view. 6, pygofer, lateral view. 7, subgenital plate, ventral view. 8, connective and styles, dorsal view. 9, style, lateral view. 10 – 12, aedeagus in lateral, dorsal, and caudal views, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217748/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">
Fig. 
<number box="[1251,1265,1440,1463]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
) elongated, 
<number box="[1403,1436,1440,1463]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" value="3.2">3.2</number>
times longer than maximum width, extending posteriorly to pygofer apex; apex rounded; ventral surface covered with minute denticuli; with fine microsetae on ventral surface along outer lateral margin. Connective (
<figureCitation box="[1186,1250,1509,1532]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1878,1902]" captionTargetBox="[226,1334,194,1804]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1334,194,1824]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Alapona modesta sp. nov., male holotype. 1, anterior portion of body, dorsal view. 2, head, frontal view. 3, anterior portion of body, lateral view. 4, forewing. 5, sternite VIII, ventral view. 6, pygofer, lateral view. 7, subgenital plate, ventral view. 8, connective and styles, dorsal view. 9, style, lateral view. 10 – 12, aedeagus in lateral, dorsal, and caudal views, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217748/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">
Fig. 
<number box="[1236,1250,1509,1532]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
) cruciform; shaft approximately as long as arms; arms curved dorsally. Style (
<figureCitation box="[815,915,1544,1567]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1878,1902]" captionTargetBox="[226,1334,194,1804]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1334,194,1824]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Alapona modesta sp. nov., male holotype. 1, anterior portion of body, dorsal view. 2, head, frontal view. 3, anterior portion of body, lateral view. 4, forewing. 5, sternite VIII, ventral view. 6, pygofer, lateral view. 7, subgenital plate, ventral view. 8, connective and styles, dorsal view. 9, style, lateral view. 10 – 12, aedeagus in lateral, dorsal, and caudal views, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217748/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">Figs 8, 9</figureCitation>
) elongate and slender, slightly curved dorsally; apical sixth strongly narrowed; apical fourth with dorsal margin flanged and serrated, projected as a long keel and short tooth preapically. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[468,592,1613,1636]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1878,1902]" captionTargetBox="[226,1334,194,1804]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1334,194,1824]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Alapona modesta sp. nov., male holotype. 1, anterior portion of body, dorsal view. 2, head, frontal view. 3, anterior portion of body, lateral view. 4, forewing. 5, sternite VIII, ventral view. 6, pygofer, lateral view. 7, subgenital plate, ventral view. 8, connective and styles, dorsal view. 9, style, lateral view. 10 – 12, aedeagus in lateral, dorsal, and caudal views, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217748/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">
Figs 
<number box="[524,592,1613,1636]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" value="11.0" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="10.0">10–12</number>
</figureCitation>
) short and stout; dorsal apodemes well developed, forming a single structure expanded laterally (resembling a pair of wings); shaft without basal elongated processes, ventral margin of apical twothirds with irregular tooth-like projections, apical third directed dorsally, forming right angle with remainder of shaft, apical half with pair of lateral triangular flanges directed ventrally; gonopore located at apex. Anal tube (segment X) without processes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,671,1985]" box="[199,391,1786,1809]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">Female unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="188" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,671,1985]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,327,1820,1844]" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species name alludes to the simplicity of the male genitalia, in comparison to 
<taxonomicName box="[1270,1383,1821,1844]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Alapona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="188" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elabora">
<emphasis box="[1270,1383,1821,1844]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="188">A. elabora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, due to the lack of ventral pygofer processes, spines on styles, and basiventral aedeagal processes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
